    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-01-15T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-01-15T11:00:00-05:00" n="711"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d711">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">394.31/1–1552: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Belgium</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Murphy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">restricted</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Brussels</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-01-15T17:00:00+01:00"
                            >January 15, 1952—5 p. m</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>975. ReDeptel 987 priority Brussels, rptd Hague 874 Lux 77 Paris 3881 Rome
                        3070.<note n="1" xml:id="d711fn1">Dated January 6, 1952, <ref
                            target="#pg_1560">p. 1560</ref>.</note>
                    <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> note on hatters fur withdrawal recd
                    Jan 15. Note reiterates Belg Govt contests applicability Article XIX and
                    notifies us Belg Govt intends request intervention of <gloss target="#t_CP1"
                        >CP</gloss>’s in accordance Article XXII [<hi rend="italic">XXIII?</hi>].
                    Note also expresses Belg Govt satisfaction with plan for assuring periodic
                    review and repeats Belg Govt reservation under paragraph 3 line A Art XIX.</p>
                <p>Sent Dept 975 rptd info Hague 64 Paris 244 Rome 43 Luxembourg unn.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Murphy</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
